<item>
            <title>[WICKET-4681] AutoLinkResolver looks in the wrong scope</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4681</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When turning on MarkupSettings#automaticLinking, AutoLinkResolver is supposed to touch tags like &amp;lt;img&amp;gt; and &amp;lt;a&amp;gt; and set their src/href attributes so that packaged resources are correctly referenced.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found a situation where that does not work: If you have a panel, and e.g. an &amp;lt;img&amp;gt; tag inside that panel, and the &amp;lt;img&amp;gt; tag is NOT enclosed in a container component, it looks for the resource in the scope of the surrounding component, not in the panel&apos;s scope. It obviously can&apos;t find it there, so it just dumps the raw attribute.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you put that &amp;lt;img&amp;gt; tag into a MarkupContainer (like WMC) then it works correctly. So it looks like the scope is off-by-one or something like that. I&apos;ll investigate.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
